00:07.125 --> 00:09.208
♪ Ben 10! ♪

00:10.458 --> 00:11.458
♪ Ben 10! ♪

00:11.542 --> 00:12.458
♪ Ben 10! ♪

00:12.542 --> 00:13.625
♪ Ben 10! ♪

00:13.708 --> 00:14.875
♪ Ben 10! ♪

00:14.958 --> 00:16.792
♪ Ben 10! ♪

00:16.875 --> 00:18.958
♪ Ben 10! ♪

00:26.875 --> 00:28.602
Max: ♪ Tomorrow today,

00:28.626 --> 00:30.375
it's on the way ♪

00:30.458 --> 00:32.185
- ♪ With your buddy, - the future's putty, ♪

00:32.292 --> 00:33.750
♪ Tomorrow today ♪

00:33.833 --> 00:35.060
Grandpa, we're the ones

00:35.084 --> 00:36.333
who are supposed to sing

00:36.417 --> 00:38.019
- the annoying songs, - not you.

00:38.125 --> 00:39.250
I can't help it.

00:39.333 --> 00:41.060
- I've wanted to visit - the Buddy Bungalow

00:41.167 --> 00:42.977
- Since I was a kid, - and finally...

00:43.083 --> 00:44.833
[ Brakes screech, bubble pops ]

00:44.917 --> 00:45.917
There it is!

00:46.000 --> 00:47.581
Do you feel it, Buddy?

00:47.605 --> 00:49.208
You're home.

00:50.292 --> 00:52.561
The Buddy Bungalow...

00:52.585 --> 00:54.875
The House of the Future.

00:54.958 --> 00:56.167
The future.

00:56.250 --> 00:58.019
Where gardeners and lawnmowers

00:58.043 --> 00:59.833
cease to exist.

00:59.917 --> 01:01.042
Weeds World.

01:01.125 --> 01:02.519
Growing soon

01:02.543 --> 01:03.958
in a sidewalk crack near you.

01:04.042 --> 01:05.769
Buddy Buddanski was a genius,

01:05.793 --> 01:07.542
a futurist.

01:07.625 --> 01:09.498
When he designed the bungalow

01:09.522 --> 01:11.417
in the '30s, it was a wonder.

01:11.500 --> 01:12.875
It brought hope to millions,

01:12.958 --> 01:14.894
- let them imagine - a better future.

01:15.000 --> 01:16.123
Once Buddy passed on,

01:16.147 --> 01:17.292
his home was closed,

01:17.375 --> 01:18.352
and his inventions

01:18.376 --> 01:19.376
were mothballed.

01:19.458 --> 01:20.685
But maybe they're finally

01:20.709 --> 01:21.958
giving tours.

01:22.042 --> 01:22.958
Hmm.

01:23.042 --> 01:24.667
Whoa. Whoa!

01:24.750 --> 01:25.750
Gwen!

01:25.792 --> 01:26.792
[ Beeping ]

01:26.875 --> 01:28.208
Aah!

01:28.292 --> 01:30.375
[ Screams ]

01:31.875 --> 01:32.998
Maybe we should do

01:33.022 --> 01:34.167
something safer,

01:34.250 --> 01:35.792
like swimming with sharks.

01:35.875 --> 01:37.333
What do you say, Grandpa?

01:37.417 --> 01:39.269
- Ugh! - Is this what we're like

01:39.375 --> 01:41.055
- When we drag him - to the amusement park?

01:41.125 --> 01:42.208
[ Beeping ]

01:42.292 --> 01:44.227
- We probably - shouldn't ask questions

01:44.333 --> 01:45.625
We don't want answers to.

01:45.708 --> 01:46.792
Let him have his fun.

01:46.875 --> 01:47.958
Grandpa?

01:48.042 --> 01:49.333
Look at all this!

01:49.417 --> 01:50.476
Buddy would bring politicians,

01:50.500 --> 01:51.740
- artists, - and scientists here

01:51.792 --> 01:53.351
- To show them - his vision of tomorrow.

01:53.375 --> 01:54.352
He was totally ahead

01:54.376 --> 01:55.376
of his time.

01:55.458 --> 01:57.167
Tomorrow today!

01:57.250 --> 01:58.458
Everyone!

01:58.542 --> 02:00.061
♪ Tomorrow today,

02:00.085 --> 02:01.625
it's on the way ♪

02:01.708 --> 02:03.519
- ♪ With your buddy, - the future's putty ♪

02:03.625 --> 02:05.292
♪ Tomorrow today ♪

02:05.375 --> 02:07.519
<i>Music Key activated.</i>

02:07.543 --> 02:09.708
<i>Presentation starting.</i>

02:09.792 --> 02:11.792
[ Gasps ]

02:11.875 --> 02:12.998
<i>Welcome to my dream for you,</i>

02:13.022 --> 02:14.167
<i>friends.</i>

02:14.250 --> 02:16.375
[ All gasp ]

02:16.458 --> 02:19.083
<i>Tomorrow starts today!</i>

02:19.167 --> 02:21.250
♪♪

02:21.333 --> 02:22.394
Oh, my gosh. Oh, my gosh.

02:22.418 --> 02:23.500
A Buddy Buggy?

02:23.583 --> 02:24.583
Come on!

02:24.625 --> 02:26.250
[ Grunts ]

02:26.333 --> 02:28.060
- How does this thing - even work?

02:28.167 --> 02:29.458
Imagination!

02:29.542 --> 02:30.790
And probably coal.

02:30.814 --> 02:32.083
It was 1930.

02:32.167 --> 02:33.208
Aah!

02:33.292 --> 02:34.582
[ Laughs ]

02:34.606 --> 02:35.917
Whoo!

02:36.000 --> 02:37.685
- Hey! - Wait for me!

02:37.792 --> 02:39.750
[ Beeping ]

02:39.833 --> 02:41.333
Ha!

02:41.417 --> 02:42.333
[ Bonk! ]

02:42.417 --> 02:43.436
Oh, come on!

02:43.460 --> 02:44.500
Huh?

02:45.042 --> 02:46.250
[ Crackling ]

02:46.333 --> 02:49.042
Oh, I get it.

02:49.125 --> 02:50.976
- They must have somebody - fixin' the place up.

02:51.000 --> 02:52.542
And not a moment too soon.

02:52.625 --> 02:54.206
Hello?

02:54.230 --> 02:55.833
Worker people?

02:55.917 --> 02:57.583
Your house stole my family.

02:57.667 --> 02:59.125
Kind of rude, actually.

02:59.208 --> 03:01.042
[ Gasps ]

03:01.125 --> 03:02.417
Steam Smythe!

03:02.500 --> 03:04.185
- Huh? - Uh, figures.

03:04.292 --> 03:05.540
If it's old and junky,

03:05.564 --> 03:06.833
you like to get funky.

03:06.917 --> 03:10.250
Uh... okay.

03:10.333 --> 03:11.644
You think you'll steal

03:11.668 --> 03:13.000
the Game Changer before me?!

03:13.083 --> 03:14.102
No clue

03:14.126 --> 03:15.167
what you're talking about,

03:15.250 --> 03:16.956
but since you're bad-guy crazy,

03:16.980 --> 03:18.708
I'm gonna stop you, anyway.

03:19.458 --> 03:21.708
[ Zip! ]

03:21.792 --> 03:23.144
Come on, Steam Smythe,

03:23.168 --> 03:24.542
gotta pick up the pace.

03:24.625 --> 03:25.519
- [ Crash! ] - Ohh!

03:25.625 --> 03:26.602
[ Sighs ]

03:26.626 --> 03:27.626
What?!

03:27.708 --> 03:29.456
<i>Remember to eat</i>

03:29.480 --> 03:31.250
<i>your vegetables.</i>

03:31.333 --> 03:32.792
Aaaaaah!

03:32.875 --> 03:35.542
Aaah! Aah! Aah! Aah!

03:39.333 --> 03:40.542
Aha!

03:40.625 --> 03:41.998
The tales are true!

03:42.022 --> 03:43.417
He <i>did</i> build it!

03:43.500 --> 03:44.833
Farewell, boy.

03:44.917 --> 03:46.769
I'm off to claim Buddanski's

03:46.793 --> 03:48.667
ultimate weapon as my own.

03:48.750 --> 03:51.417
Aaaaah!

03:51.500 --> 03:53.206
Ultimate weapon?

03:53.230 --> 03:54.958
That doesn't sound good.

03:57.417 --> 03:58.833
[ Whirring ]

03:58.917 --> 04:00.082
Uh,

04:00.106 --> 04:01.292
I don't have the words.

04:01.375 --> 04:03.686
<i>A bright new day starts</i>

04:03.710 --> 04:06.042
<i>in the bathroom of the future!</i>

04:08.667 --> 04:09.936
It's just like I dreamed

04:09.960 --> 04:11.250
when I was a kid.

04:11.333 --> 04:12.417
That people in a buggy

04:12.500 --> 04:14.180
- would watch you get showered - by robots?

04:14.208 --> 04:16.083
<i>Ready to floss your way to fun?</i>

04:16.167 --> 04:17.748
<i>Today, the future tastes</i>

04:17.772 --> 04:19.375
<i>like spearmint...</i>

04:19.458 --> 04:21.042
<i>toothpaste, that is.</i>

04:21.125 --> 04:22.292
[ Splat! ]

04:22.375 --> 04:24.144
- Dental hygiene - and rusty electronics

04:24.250 --> 04:25.958
Are not a good mix...

04:26.042 --> 04:27.583
Whoa-oh-oh-oh!

04:27.667 --> 04:28.977
This is just like

04:29.001 --> 04:30.333
a real Buddanski Adventure!

04:30.417 --> 04:31.458
Aaaah!

04:31.542 --> 04:32.542
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

04:32.625 --> 04:33.708
Whaa! Aah!

04:33.792 --> 04:35.417
Whee!

04:35.500 --> 04:37.750
Whoa, whoa, whoa, aah!

04:37.833 --> 04:39.917
Aah!

04:40.667 --> 04:41.707
<i>Make sure you brush</i>

04:41.731 --> 04:42.792
<i>after every meal.</i>

04:42.875 --> 04:45.060
- [ Whimpers ] - That won't give me nightmares.

04:45.167 --> 04:46.208
Not at all.

04:46.292 --> 04:47.292
Hmm.

04:47.333 --> 04:48.977
- Uh, maybe this is getting - out of hand.

04:49.083 --> 04:51.000
Oh, hold on.

04:51.083 --> 04:52.269
I think I can steer

04:52.293 --> 04:53.500
the buggy from down here,

04:53.583 --> 04:55.227
- but I can't see - where we're going.

04:55.333 --> 04:56.792
Now! Turn now!

04:56.875 --> 04:58.958
Waah!

05:01.375 --> 05:02.811
All this chaos just so you can

05:02.835 --> 05:04.292
dig up some old weapon?

05:04.375 --> 05:05.625
Steam Smythe?!

05:05.708 --> 05:06.706
We have to go help Be...

05:06.730 --> 05:07.750
Aah!

05:07.833 --> 05:09.333
[ Both scream ]

05:09.417 --> 05:10.625
[ Tires squeal ]

05:10.708 --> 05:12.060
You've already got a bunch

05:12.084 --> 05:13.458
of crusty, old weapons.

05:13.542 --> 05:14.768
- What's so great - about this one?

05:14.792 --> 05:15.957
You are ignorant as ever,

05:15.981 --> 05:17.167
boy!

05:17.250 --> 05:18.602
On the surface,

05:18.626 --> 05:20.000
Buddanski was a showman

05:20.083 --> 05:21.248
entertaining

05:21.272 --> 05:22.458
the drooling masses.

05:24.667 --> 05:26.310
- [ Sniffs ] - Hyah!

05:26.417 --> 05:28.250
[ Grunts ]

05:28.333 --> 05:29.625
Ah! Cozy.

05:29.708 --> 05:31.185
But secretly,

05:31.209 --> 05:32.708
Buddanski was building this,

05:32.792 --> 05:34.415
a magnificent weapon...

05:34.439 --> 05:36.083
The M.F.B.!

05:36.167 --> 05:37.790
Mmrph! Bleh!

05:37.814 --> 05:39.458
Fascinating!

05:39.542 --> 05:40.542
Monologue me more.

05:40.583 --> 05:42.375
For all of his insipid talk,

05:42.458 --> 05:43.894
Buddanski saw a future

05:43.918 --> 05:45.375
of warfare and strife.

05:45.458 --> 05:47.894
He built the M.F.B. in secret,

05:47.918 --> 05:50.375
in case it was ever needed.

05:50.458 --> 05:51.625
Whoa!

05:51.708 --> 05:53.206
Today, his genius

05:53.230 --> 05:54.750
will give me the power

05:54.833 --> 05:57.456
to wash away all modern

05:57.480 --> 06:00.125
technology in one flush!

06:02.958 --> 06:04.060
[ Coughs ]

06:04.084 --> 06:05.208
Hmph!

06:06.375 --> 06:07.500
Ugh!

06:07.583 --> 06:09.019
This 90-year-old toilet water

06:09.043 --> 06:10.500
smells like...

06:10.583 --> 06:12.583
90-year-old toilet water.

06:12.667 --> 06:13.977
[ Gags ]

06:14.001 --> 06:15.333
Ah, better.

06:15.417 --> 06:17.394
Yoo-hoo!

06:17.418 --> 06:19.417
Where are you?

06:19.500 --> 06:21.248
You want to save

06:21.272 --> 06:23.042
this dilapidated world?

06:23.125 --> 06:25.458
Come and get me, boy.

06:25.542 --> 06:26.875
Done and done!

06:26.958 --> 06:29.375
[ Panting ]

06:29.458 --> 06:31.792
[ Whirring ]

06:31.875 --> 06:33.917
<i>Buddanski turbine activated.</i>

06:34.000 --> 06:35.540
Say what, now?

06:35.564 --> 06:37.125
Aah! No brakes!

06:37.208 --> 06:39.208
Whoa! Whoa! Aah!

06:39.292 --> 06:40.583
[ Laughs evilly ]

06:40.667 --> 06:42.082
The M.F.B. powers up

06:42.106 --> 06:43.542
by turbine.

06:43.625 --> 06:44.998
It would've taken me weeks

06:45.022 --> 06:46.417
to awaken it alone.

06:46.500 --> 06:48.352
Your adolescent gusto has

06:48.376 --> 06:50.250
given me gigawatts of energy,

06:50.333 --> 06:51.560
and all without lifting

06:51.584 --> 06:52.833
a finger.

06:52.917 --> 06:53.917
[ Laughs evilly ]

06:54.000 --> 06:55.581
[ Sighs ]

06:55.605 --> 06:57.208
Duped by a doofus!

06:57.292 --> 06:58.583
Splendid!

06:58.667 --> 07:01.123
The Age of Steam is upon us,

07:01.147 --> 07:03.625
courtesy of the future.

07:03.708 --> 07:04.917
[ Grunts ]

07:05.000 --> 07:07.083
[ Beeping ]

07:10.000 --> 07:11.456
How tiny was Buddanski,

07:11.480 --> 07:12.958
anyway?

07:13.042 --> 07:14.208
Skazadoosh!

07:14.292 --> 07:15.375
Wha...

07:15.458 --> 07:17.167
Whoa! So weird.

07:17.250 --> 07:18.706
Kid-sized hatch.

07:18.730 --> 07:20.208
Kid-sized controls.

07:20.292 --> 07:21.998
Was Buddanski making weapons

07:22.022 --> 07:23.750
for kid-sized bad guys?

07:23.833 --> 07:25.583
[ Tink! ]

07:25.667 --> 07:27.602
- Everything Grandpa said - makes me think

07:27.708 --> 07:28.790
This place is designed

07:28.814 --> 07:29.917
to excite a kid.

07:30.000 --> 07:31.540
The world's oldest kid has been

07:31.564 --> 07:33.125
teaching me that all day.

07:33.208 --> 07:34.500
Ludicrous!

07:34.583 --> 07:35.935
Why would he build a weapon

07:35.959 --> 07:37.333
to be piloted by a child?

07:37.417 --> 07:39.144
Buddanski knew that the future

07:39.168 --> 07:40.917
belongs to men with power...

07:41.000 --> 07:42.935
- Power that belongs - to me now!

07:43.042 --> 07:44.665
If this thing is a weapon,

07:44.689 --> 07:46.333
I have to destroy it.

07:46.417 --> 07:47.936
Steam Smythe: Go on! Do it!

07:47.960 --> 07:49.500
Prove me right!

07:49.583 --> 07:51.519
Activate the weapon and behold

07:51.543 --> 07:53.500
the end of tomorrow!

07:53.583 --> 07:55.727
- Grandpa said Buddy brought hope - to millions,

07:55.833 --> 07:57.167
Imagined a better future.

07:57.250 --> 07:58.894
Whatever Buddy built,

07:58.918 --> 08:00.583
it wasn't to hurt people.

08:00.667 --> 08:01.667
[ Machine hums ]

08:01.750 --> 08:03.833
<i>Game-changer activated.</i>

08:08.292 --> 08:09.810
- -Whoa! - -Whoa!

08:09.917 --> 08:11.500
[ Screams ]

08:11.583 --> 08:13.708
Aah!

08:18.750 --> 08:20.125
Whoa.

08:20.208 --> 08:21.500
Admiring the view?

08:21.583 --> 08:22.875
Aah! Let go!

08:22.958 --> 08:24.208
Of course!

08:24.292 --> 08:25.686
Wha...

08:25.710 --> 08:27.125
[ Grunts ]

08:27.208 --> 08:30.167
♪♪

08:36.292 --> 08:37.583
Are you okay?

08:37.667 --> 08:39.250
I'm fine, Grandpa.

08:39.333 --> 08:40.500
Huh?

08:40.583 --> 08:41.685
Oh.

08:41.709 --> 08:42.833
It's amazing.

08:42.917 --> 08:44.458
It's Ben!

08:44.542 --> 08:47.292
[ Grunting ]

08:51.042 --> 08:53.458
This is the M.F.B.?

08:53.542 --> 08:55.477
- How does one destroy - civilization

08:55.583 --> 08:57.625
With a Ferris wheel?

08:57.708 --> 08:58.935
<i>Hey, future.</i>

08:58.959 --> 09:00.208
<i>Welcome to the M.F.B,</i>

09:00.292 --> 09:01.750
<i>a real game changer!</i>

09:01.833 --> 09:03.060
<i>The brave men and women</i>

09:03.084 --> 09:04.333
<i>defending our country</i>

09:04.417 --> 09:06.060
<i>- are in need - of a little family fun,</i>

09:06.167 --> 09:07.667
<i>So the U.S. Army asked</i>

09:07.750 --> 09:08.915
<i>if I could bring the fun</i>

09:08.939 --> 09:10.125
<i>to them!</i>

09:10.208 --> 09:12.500
<i>Unfortunately, the Army decided</i>

09:12.583 --> 09:13.581
<i>to build tanks and bombs</i>

09:13.605 --> 09:14.625
<i>instead,</i>

09:14.708 --> 09:17.250
<i>but I built the M.F.B. anyway,</i>

09:17.333 --> 09:18.977
<i>hoping that one day</i>

09:19.001 --> 09:20.667
<i>a special someone would find it</i>

09:20.750 --> 09:22.186
<i>and use it to bring hope</i>

09:22.210 --> 09:23.667
<i>to those who need it most.</i>

09:23.750 --> 09:25.290
<i>And you're watching this,</i>

09:25.314 --> 09:26.875
<i>so you did it!</i>

09:26.958 --> 09:28.852
<i>Enjoy the future,</i>

09:28.876 --> 09:30.792
<i>and the Mobile Fun Base.</i>

09:30.875 --> 09:34.000
Mobile... fun... base.

09:34.083 --> 09:36.000
That can't be right!

09:36.083 --> 09:37.917
Cornblisters, Buddanski!

09:38.000 --> 09:39.290
What a wasted genius.

09:39.314 --> 09:40.625
[ Grumbles ]

09:40.708 --> 09:41.748
Don't worry, Ben!

09:41.772 --> 09:42.833
I've got you!

09:42.917 --> 09:45.207
Well, if he wanted this

09:45.231 --> 09:47.542
automaton to have some fun,

09:47.625 --> 09:50.625
then let's have some fun!

09:53.083 --> 09:55.250
[ Laughs evilly ]

09:55.333 --> 09:57.102
I'll make

09:57.126 --> 09:58.917
a war machine of you yet!

10:00.958 --> 10:01.875
Aaaaaah!

10:01.958 --> 10:04.042
Ben! Ben!

10:05.417 --> 10:06.790
Buddy said this machine

10:06.814 --> 10:08.208
was for fun, not war!

10:08.292 --> 10:10.125
Oh, but I <i>am</i> having fun.

10:10.208 --> 10:11.458
And pretty soon,

10:11.542 --> 10:12.790
the whole world will know

10:12.814 --> 10:14.083
how fun I can be.

10:14.167 --> 10:15.623
Well, your definition

10:15.647 --> 10:17.125
of fun stinks,

10:17.208 --> 10:18.500
and so do you.

10:18.583 --> 10:19.958
[ Splat! ]

10:20.042 --> 10:21.625
[ Whirl! ]

10:21.708 --> 10:25.167
Whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa-whoa!

10:25.250 --> 10:26.331
Whoa-whoa-whoa!

10:26.355 --> 10:27.458
Aah!

10:27.542 --> 10:29.125
[ Grunts ]

10:29.208 --> 10:30.458
[ Splat! ]

10:30.542 --> 10:31.790
<i>Emergency escape protocol</i>

10:31.814 --> 10:33.083
<i>initiated.</i>

10:33.167 --> 10:35.250
Emergency what?

10:36.375 --> 10:37.375
[ Grumbles ]

10:37.417 --> 10:39.186
I tire of losing

10:39.210 --> 10:41.000
to 10-year-olds!

10:41.083 --> 10:42.935
- Ben. - You okay?

10:43.042 --> 10:44.394
Yeppers. Survived

10:44.418 --> 10:45.792
the walking amusement park.

10:45.875 --> 10:48.165
Buddy was a special

10:48.189 --> 10:50.500
kind of genius, for sure.

10:50.583 --> 10:52.102
- Are we gonna sit around - jabbering,

10:52.208 --> 10:53.185
Or are we gonna ride

10:53.209 --> 10:54.209
this thing?

10:54.292 --> 10:55.811
[ Children cheering ]

10:54.292 --> 10:57.375
it's on the way ♪

10:55.835 --> 10:57.458
♪ Tomorrow today,

10:57.458 --> 10:59.018
- ♪ With your buddy, - the future's putty ♪

10:59.042 --> 11:01.125
♪ Tomorrow today ♪

11:02.125 --> 11:04.208
♪♪

11:14.042 --> 11:16.417
Time to throw stuff!
